Child abuse is a rather common cause of injuries and emergency situations in children. Therefore, it is indispensable for everyone who attends emergencies with children involved to know the possible signs and symptoms of abuse. There are very few safe signs of child abuse, but a large variety of injuries, symptoms and anamnestic data which should lead one to suspect abuse. It is important to establish whether abuse could be the cause of injuries of a child in an emergency situation. Differential diagnoses for possible signs of child abuse are mentioned.  
